      "Before you spend a dollar on paid traffic, run this audit. A landing page with conversion blockers turns ad spend into waste. Fix these 15 issues first — then scale.",
      "Message match (critical): The headline on your landing page must match the ad copy or organic keyword that brought the visitor. A visitor who clicked an ad for fast website audits should land on a page with that exact language — not your generic homepage. Mismatched messaging is the single biggest cause of high bounce rates from paid traffic.",
      "Clarity of value proposition: Can a first-time visitor understand in 5 seconds what you offer, who it is for, and why they should care? Test with the 5-second test — show the page to someone unfamiliar, hide it after 5 seconds, and ask them what they understand. If they cannot explain it, your hero section needs work.",
      "Single CTA focus: Landing pages with multiple CTAs (Book a call AND Sign up AND Learn more) dilute attention. High-performing landing pages have one primary action. If you must offer multiple options, use visual hierarchy to make one dominant.",
      "Social proof near the CTA: Testimonials, star ratings, client logos, and case study numbers placed near the conversion point increase trust at the moment of decision. Generic social proof at the bottom of the page is almost useless — put it where it matters.",
      "Form friction audit: Count your form fields. Every field beyond name and email reduces submissions. Ask: do you actually need company size on the initial form? Job title? Budget? The information you want is worth less than the conversion you are losing. Collect more data after the initial conversion.",
      "Mobile conversion parity: If your desktop conversion rate is 3% but mobile is 0.8%, something is broken on mobile. Check tap target sizes, form input types (use tel for phone, email for email — this triggers the right keyboard on mobile), and button placement relative to the fold on small screens.",
      "Page speed at conversion: A one-second delay in page load reduces conversions by 7%. Landing pages receiving paid traffic should load in under 2 seconds. Use a CDN. Optimize images. Defer non-critical JavaScript. Test with PageSpeed Insights on both mobile and desktop.",
      "Trust signals: SSL certificate visible in browser. Privacy policy link near forms. Physical address or company registration (especially important for professional services). Money-back guarantee or risk reversal language. Real team photos or company photos (not stock images).",
      "Tracking setup: Before spending money, verify: conversion tracking fires on form submission (not just page load). Google Ads conversion tracking is linked. GA4 has a key event for this conversion. You can segment conversions by traffic source. Without this, you cannot optimize.",
