      "TikTok's algorithm is the most powerful organic distribution engine in social media today. A new account can reach 100,000 people with one well-timed video. But most businesses either dismiss it as irrelevant or post corporate content that gets zero views.",
      "Who TikTok actually works for in 2025: Service businesses that can demonstrate expertise visually (interior designers, chefs, fitness coaches, web developers). E-commerce brands with visually interesting products. B2B companies whose target audience skews under 40. Local businesses showing behind-the-scenes operations. Media and content businesses building audience for newsletters or courses.",
      "Content formats that work for non-entertainment businesses: Educational reveals (the thing everyone in your industry gets wrong). Process videos (showing the steps behind your work). Before-and-after (renovation, web design, transformation content). Reaction videos to industry news or common misconceptions. Answering customer questions directly (the TikTok version of FAQ).",
      "The TikTok algorithm explained: Unlike Instagram and LinkedIn which favor accounts with existing followers, TikTok distributes to non-followers based on content quality. Every video is tested with a small audience first. If it performs above threshold (watch time, comments, shares, replays), it gets distributed wider. This means a brand-new account can go viral; an established account can post content that nobody sees. Quality always beats frequency.",
      "Hook in the first 2 seconds: TikTok's defining challenge — the first 2 seconds determine whether viewers swipe past or keep watching. Effective hooks: start mid-action, not with an intro. Lead with the most interesting part. Use text overlays that create curiosity. Ask a question the target audience wants answered. Avoid: logos, intros, music without voiceover.",
      "TikTok vs Instagram Reels vs YouTube Shorts: All three platforms push short-form video, but algorithms differ. TikTok has the highest organic reach for new accounts. Reels reach existing Instagram followers better, making it more valuable for established accounts. YouTube Shorts benefit from search intent — shorts appear in YouTube searches, giving them longer shelf life.",
      "TikTok Ads for business: TikTok ads work best for products with mass market appeal and visually demonstrable benefits. B2B and high-ticket services typically see better ROI from LinkedIn. The minimum budget for meaningful TikTok Ads testing is $50/day for at least 2 weeks. In-feed video ads perform better than TopView for direct response.",
      "At Codeworth, we help clients build social media presence that complements their website strategy — creating content that drives traffic, builds authority, and converts viewers into leads.",
